## 7. Student Engagement Tasks  

**Task 1:**  
Identify one information system you use daily and describe it using the five-component model.

**Task 2:**  
Find a recent news article describing a digital system failure (e.g., bank outage, airline disruption). Identify whether the failure was primarily technical, procedural, or human.

Suggested source:  
https://www.bbc.com/news/technology

---

## 8. Key Takeaways  

This lecture establishes the conceptual foundation for the course. Students should understand that:
- Information systems are more than just technology.
- Data only becomes valuable through processing and interpretation.
- Effective management requires systems literacy rather than programming expertise.

